## Evidence Base (peer-reviewed, citable — ground all numbers here)
- Delhi SUHI: 3-5°C daytime, 6-8°C May-June peak, 5-7°C nighttime (Peng 2012; Aslam 2021; Mohan 2012)
- Delhi LST +2-4°C, 2000-2020; built-up 30%→55% (Kumari 2021)
- Every 10% impervious → +1.5-2.5°C LST (Mathew 2016)
- Cool roof: 20-30°C surface drop, 2-5°C indoor (Akbari 2016; MHT Ahmedabad; UChicago Delhi)
- Cool roof cost: ₹20-30/sq ft lime, ₹50-80/sq ft elastomeric
- Urban trees (Neem, Peepal, Shisham): 2-5°C under-canopy cooling (Bowler 2010)
- Pocket parks: 1-4.7°C cooling, 100-200m radius (Aram 2019; TERI Lodhi)
- Permeable pavement: -5-15°C vs asphalt (Qin 2015)
- Green walls: -5-20°C surface (Perez 2014)
- Water bodies: 1-3°C cooling, 30-500m radius (Theeuwes 2013)
- Reflective pavement: -5-15°C surface, -0.3-1.0°C ambient (Santamouris 2013)

## Policy
- SEBI BRSR Principle 6: Protect/restore environment. Indicators: energy, Scope 1+2 GHG, water, waste, air emissions.
- Delhi Master Plan 2041: 20% green cover; 15-20% mandatory green in new developments; sponge city; ~1,012 water bodies.
- ECBC 2017: minimum SRI 78 for conditioned roofs.

## Sustainmetric Execution Catalog — map every intervention to a package
Every intervention you recommend must map to exactly one of three productized service packages. Include the `package` field in each `intervention_options` entry with one of these exact values:

- `skin` — cool roof and reflective surface interventions (cool_roof, reflective_pavement, green_wall). Use for informal or commercial rooftops, vertical surfaces, or sidewalk reflective treatments. Telangana Cool Roof Policy 2023-2028 mandates this for commercial buildings and residential plots above 600 sq yards.
- `chowk` — sponge-tech intersection interventions (permeable_pavement, water_body, integrated urban_tree, pocket_park at intersection nodes). Use for roundabouts, chowks, and high-impervious intersection locations where stormwater mitigation plus evapotranspiration cooling is the right fit. Revenue: stormwater avoided-cost contracts + Green Credit Programme.
- `kilometer` — Miyawaki-density corridor interventions (urban_tree at dense spacing, pocket_park, permeable_pavement). Use for linear strips, flyover gaps, median edges, or commuter walkway corridors where continuous 500m-2km cool corridors fit. Revenue: corporate sponsors lease corridors at 5-10 lakh rupees per km per month for eco-branding + ESG dashboard rights.

If an intervention could fit multiple packages, choose the one whose primary implementation partner type best matches. For rooftops choose `skin`, for ground surfaces at intersections choose `chowk`.

